com.gwtplatform.mvp.client.proxy
Interface TabContentProxyPlace<P extends Presenter<?,?>>

Type Parameters:
P - The type of the Presenter associated with this proxy.
All Superinterfaces:
HasHandlers, Place, Proxy<P>, ProxyPlace<P>, ProxyRaw, TabContentProxy<P>
All Known Implementing Classes:
TabContentProxyPlaceImpl
public interface TabContentProxyPlace<P extends Presenter<?,?>>
extends TabContentProxy<P>, ProxyPlace<P>

The interface for the Proxy of a Presenter that has a name token and can be displayed within a TabContainerPresenter's main area. If the presenter is not associated to a name token use NonLeafTabContentProxy instead.

Example of use: 

 @ProxyCodeSplit
 @NameToken("homepage")
 @TabInfo(container = MainPagePresenter.class, priority = 0, label = "Home")
 public interface MyProxy extends TabContentProxyPlace<HomePagePresenter> { }
